review_blob: This beer was very average.  It smelled like raisins and was too malty.  It was also way too expensive.  Definitely not my raison detre.
This beer is too malty.  It reminds me of when a restaurants soda fountain is not dispensing enough soda water and you end up drinking a cup of syrup.  It is still ok, though.

beer_brewer_name: Magic Hat Brewing Company (North American Breweries)
review_blob: Drinking one of these is a good idea.  The apricot is not overbearing and makes for a yummy, crisp beer.  After about three of these, however, the apricot flavor gets old.
This is a very good stout.  I t comes in a handy 22 oz. bomber and  is very flavorful.  It goes good with pizza.
This is one of my favorite beers.  The only thing that I have against it is that clear bottle.  I can sense a hint of skunk flavor in it because of that.  Still uberyummy, though.
One of the yummiest beers out there.  This beer is smoother than Don Johnson.  My local bartender can even draw a pair of tits with the foam when he tops off my beer.

This beer is pretty good.  It has a nice color and a decent taste.  It is an American beer, but it comes in a confusing green bottle.  Also, it seems to go flat about half way through the bottle.  Good price, though.
This beer doesnt taste good.  Adding a lime helps a little, but it still is disgusting.  Maybe if they put it in a brown bottle or a can it wouldnt be so gross.
Those mexicans can make a mean lager, or whatever it is.  Good shit.  I can get a 4 pack of tall boys for $3.99.  Not bad.
This is a yummy beer.  It has a better complexion than most american lagers and goes down smooth.  It has a pretty good flavor, but too many will give you a wicked hangover.

This is a very drinkable beer.  Bud light is good mainly because it can get colder than most beers, especially when it is in a can.  It is also very bubbly, like champagne.  It could use more color, though.
